{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f187aecc-d29f-4846-9192-b3ddf5aed821","content":"In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. You override `CreateWindow` in your `App` class and use a custom `Window`:\n\n```csharp\n// App.xaml.cs\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new AppShell());\n\n    window.Created += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnStart */ };\n    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnSleep */ };\n    window.Resumed += (s, e) => { /* replaces OnResume */ };\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\nOr subclass `Window` and override `OnCreated()`, `OnStopped()`, `OnResumed()` directly.\n\n**Mapping summary:**\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI Window |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `Created` / `OnCreated()` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `Stopped` / `OnStopped()` |\n| `OnResume()` | `Resumed` / `OnResumed()` |\n\nThere are also `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Destroying`, and `Backgrounding` events for finer-grained control.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edf24b0e-9774-492c-9c7e-4a3e0b839def","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. Instead of those overrides, you use the `Window` lifecycle events or the cross-platform lifecycle events via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`, or you can override `CreateWindow()` and hook into `Window` events.\n\n\nThe mappings are straightforward: `OnStart` becomes `Window.Created`, `OnSleep` maps to `Window.Deactivated` or `Window.Stopped`, and `OnResume` corresponds to `Window.Resumed` or `Window.Activated`. You can hook into these through `ILifecycleEventHandler` or directly on the window's lifecycle events, since the `Application` class in MAUI doesn't have those virtual methods anymore.","outputTokens":774,"requestId":"3C2D:7C3A8:D837C1:10C6331:6A0129E0"},"id":"5de14271-e330-4aac-8f47-dee0ce1b6313","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:27.402Z","parentId":"cb6d84a0-2787-45c9-899a-f22d373aac29"}
